  <!-- 2. THE SHIFT -->
  <section id="the-shift">
    <div class="card reveal">
      <span class="section-label section-label--filled">What Changed</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">AI didn't replace developers. It created new&nbsp;ones.</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">There's a principle called <strong>Jevons Paradox</strong>: when something gets cheaper, people don't use less of it. They use more.</p>
      <p style="max-width: 38em; color: var(--gray-dark);">When lighting got cheaper, cities lit up. When travel got cheaper, people went everywhere. When communication got cheaper, social media was born. The pattern holds: lower the cost of creation, and you don't get less. You get an&nbsp;explosion.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid-4 reveal">
